the%20study.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20AI%20tool%20could%20decipher%20text%20%E2%80%94%20including%20passwords%20%E2%80%94%20from%20keystroke%20sounds%20recorded%20over%20Zoom%20and%20be%20right%20over%20nine%20times%20out%20of%20ten%2C%20a%20group%20of%20researchers%20said%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2308.01074%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20paper%20published%20on%20August%203%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20AI%20model%20developed%20by%20the%20researchers%20showed%20a%2093%25%20accuracy%20rate%20in%20deciphering%20keystrokes%20from%20a%20recording%20of%20a%20Macbook's%20keystrokes%20made%20over%20video%20conferencing%20software%20Zoom%2C%20according%20to%20a%20group%20of%20researchers%20affiliated%20with%20Durham%20University%2C%20the%20University%20of%20Surrey%2C%20and%20the%20Royal%20Holloway%20University%20of%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20accuracy%20rate%20rose%20to%2095%25%20when%20keystrokes%20were%20recorded%20using%20an%20iPhone%2013%20mini.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAcoustic%20side-channel%20attacks%26quot%3B%20are%20a%20growing%20threat%20to%20keyboards%2C%20the%20researchers%20said.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fwhat-is-side-channel-attack%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESide-channel%20attacks%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0are%20used%20by%20hackers%20to%20exploit%20information%20%E2%80%94%20like%20how%20much%20power%20your%20computer%20is%20using%20or%20the%20keystroke%20sounds%20it%20makes%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20than%20directly%20attacking%20the%20system's%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20their%20experiment%2C%20the%20team%20used%20a%202021%2016-inch%20MacBook%20Pro%2C%20highlighting%20its%20consistent%20keyboard%20design%20with%20other%20recent%20MacBook%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20AI%20tool%20was%20based%20on%20%26quot%3Bdeep%20learning%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20subset%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-machine-learning%5C%22%3Emachine%20learning%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20trains%20computers%20to%20analyze%20data%20similarly%20to%20how%20the%20human%20brain%20functions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20also%20highlighted%20potential%20countermeasures.%20%26quot%3BPasswords%20containing%20full%20words%20may%20be%20at%20greater%20risk%20of%20attack%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20study's%20authors.%20Touch%20typing%20and%20adding%20background%20noise%20also%20seemed%20to%20lower%20the%20accuracy%20rate%20of%20the%20AI%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20said%20that%20while%20these%20types%20of%20attacks%20are%20under-studied%2C%20they%20have%20a%20long%20history.%20%26quot%3BAcoustic%20emanations%26quot%3B%20were%20even%20mentioned%20as%20a%20vulnerability%20in%20a%201982%20partially%20declassified%20NSA%20document%2C%20the%20authors%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20adds%20to%20recent%20concerns%20over%20how%20AI%20tools%20could%20be%20used%20to%20compromise%20security%20and%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20tools%20can%20make%20online%20scams%20harder%20to%20detect%20because%20AI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-scam-spam-hacking-ruining-internet-chatgpt-privacy-misinformation-2023-8%5C%22%3Emakes%20it%20easier%20to%20personalize%20scams%20for%20each%20target%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Insider%20reported%20last%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20specialists%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fari-mahairas-and-peter-beshar-on-ai-and-5g-security-risks-2019-5%5C%22%3Eraised%20the%20alarm%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202019%20over%20how%20the%20advancement%20of%20AI%20and%205G%20technology%20would%20heighten%20vulnerabilities%20in%20internet-connected%20devices%2C%20amplifying%20cybersecurity%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study's%20authors%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Insider%2C%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-decipher-passwords-hackers-listening-keystrokes-zoom-study-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692156510000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dc37034ef9f30019f7b44a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-decipher-passwords-hackers-listening-keystrokes-zoom-study-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22These%20%26quot%3Bacoustic%20side-channel%20attacks%26quot%3B%20present%20a%20greater%20threat%20to%20keyboards%20than%20ever%20before%2C%20said%20the%20researchers%20in%20their%20paper.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kteo%40insider.com%20(Kai%20Xiang%20Teo)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-decipher-passwords-hackers-listening-keystrokes-zoom-study-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Why'd%20it%20have%20to%20be%20snakes%3F'%20-%20New%20species%20of%20serpent%20named%20after%20Harrison%20Ford%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692156360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F06%2F768x432%2Fskynews-harrison-ford-indiana-jones_6187915.jpg%3F20230615094835%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwhyd-it-have-to-be-snakes-new-species-of-serpent-named-after-harrison-ford-12940904%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20new%20species%20of%20snake%20has%20been%20named%20after%20Harrison%20Ford.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwhyd-it-have-to-be-snakes-new-species-of-serpent-named-after-harrison-ford-12940904%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fwhyd-it-have-to-be-snakes-new-species-of-serpent-named-after-harrison-ford-12940904%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2F