80%9CThis%20is%20an%20area%20where%20we%20have%20always%20respected%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20religions.%20When%20the%20%5BShobha%5D%20Yatra%20reached%20the%20mosque%2C%20we%20saw%20Hindus%20chanting%20%E2%80%98Jai%20Shree%20Ram%E2%80%99%20and%20waving%20swords%20and%20sticks.%20We%20offered%20them%20water%20respectfully%2C%20as%20they%20were%20doing%20their%20religious%20duty%2C%E2%80%9D%20Khalid%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhalid%20also%20says%20that%20many%20non-Muslim%20patients%20from%20the%20hospital%20would%20come%20this%20masjid%20to%20bathe%20and%20get%20water%20when%20there%20was%20a%20shortage%20at%20the%20hospital.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20nothing%20called%20Hindu-Muslim%20problems%20here%2C%20we%20have%20lived%20in%20peace%20and%20still%20want%20to%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20loss%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAas%20Mohammed%2C%20a%20security%20guard%20at%20the%20nearby%20medical%20college%2C%20recently%20lost%20a%20part%20of%20his%20home%20to%20the%20Haryana%20government%E2%80%99s%20demolition%20drive%20that%20closely%20followed%20the%20communal%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohammed%2C%2057%2C%20whose%20son%20ran%20a%20tea%20shack%20near%20the%20college%2C%20also%20saw%20his%20own%20shop%20being%20flattened%20by%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20bulldozers.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20didn%E2%80%99t%20even%20give%20us%20a%20minute%20to%20vacate%20or%20at%20least%20grab%20our%20belongings.%20They%20just%20tore%20it%20all%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20Many%20homes%20and%20shops%2C%20like%20that%20of%20Mohammed%E2%80%99s%2C%20could%20not%20be%20saved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohammed%20also%20says%20that%20his%20own%20amity%20with%20Hindus%20has%20always%20remained%20pristine.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20seen%20tough%20times%2C%20when%20Muslim%20lives%20were%20vulnerable.%20I%20was%20here%20in%201992%2C%20when%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20was%20torn%20down%2C%20and%20I%20am%20here%20today.%20We%20supported%20Hindus%20back%20then%2C