ion%3EIncrease%20your%20computer's%20FPS%20with%20these%20tips%20to%20optimize%20your%20gaming.%3Cp%3EMatei%20Alexandru%20Marcu%2FEyeEm%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EYou%20can%20increase%20FPS%20%E2%80%94%20frames%20per%20second%20%E2%80%94%20by%20optimizing%20game%20settings%20on%20your%20computer.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFrame%20rate%20is%20a%20measure%20of%20how%20smoothly%20games%20and%20graphically%20intense%20visuals%20display%20on%20your%20PC.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIf%20FPS%20is%20lower%20than%20your%20monitor's%20refresh%20rate%2C%20you%20may%20be%20able%20to%20improve%20performance.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFrames%20per%20second%2C%20or%20FPS%2C%20is%20a%20common%20metric%20used%20to%20judge%20your%20gaming%20PC's%20performance.%20FPS%20denotes%20how%20many%20image%20frames%20are%20rendered%20and%20displayed%20every%20second%20during%20gameplay.%20For%20instance%20a%20game%20playing%20at%2060%20FPS%20will%20render%2060%20individual%20frames%20consecutively%20every%20second.%C2%A0%20Higher%20frame%20rates%20generally%20lead%20to%20smoother%20animations%20and%20gameplay.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20console%20games%20on%20Xbox%2C%20PlayStation%2C%20and%20Switch%20are%20typically%20locked%20to%20a%20specific%20frame%20rate%2C%20PC%20gamers%20can%20adjust%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20settings%20to%20get%20more%20FPS.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-gaming-pc%5C%22%3Ebest%20gaming%20PCs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-gaming-laptop%5C%22%3Ebest%20gaming%20laptops%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20come%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-a-graphics-card%5C%22%3Egraphics%20cards%3C%2Fa%3E%20designed%20to%20optimize%20games%20for%20higher%20FPS%2C%20but%20performance%20can%20vary%20a%20lot%20depending%20on%20what%20kind%20of%20hardware%20your%20computer%20is%20running.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20experiencing%20gaming%20lag%20or%20stutters%2C%20you%20might%20need%20to%20tweak%20your%20PC%20to%20improve%20the%20frame%20rate.%20Thankfully%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20simple%20steps%20you%20can%20take%20that%20could%20help%20boost%20your%20FPS%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20to%20increase%20FPS%20on%20your%20computer%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20increase%20FPS%20on%20your%20computer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20seven%20tips%20and%20troubleshooting%20tricks%20for%20boosting%20your%20computer's%20gaming%20performance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Find%20your%20monitor's%20refresh%20rate%5C%22%3EFind%20your%20monitor's%20refresh%20rate%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20stats%20you%20should%20know%20before%20you%20start%20tweaking%20your%20PC%3A%20Your%20current%20frame%20rate%2C%20expressed%20in%20frames%20per%20second%20(FPS)%2C%20and%20the%20monitor's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fmonitor-refresh-rate%5C%22%3Erefresh%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20measured%20in%20hertz%20(Hz).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20refresh%20rate%20is%20easy%20to%20find%2C%20so%20we'll%20start%20there.%20Most%20monitors%20and%20TVs%20have%20a%20refresh%20rate%20of%2060Hz%20or%20120Hz%2C%20while%20new%20gaming%20monitors%20and%20laptops%20support%20much%20higher%20refresh%20rates%2C%20such%20as%20144Hz%2C%20240Hz%2C%20or%20even%20360Hz.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20frame%20rate%20that%20matches%20your%20refresh%20rate%20will%20create%20smoother%20animation%3B%20for%20example%2C%20if%20your%20computer%20is%20running%20at%2060%20FPS%20on%20a%2060Hz%20monitor%2C%20the%20display%20will%20have%20a%20fresh%20frame%20of%20animation%20every%20time%20it%20updates%20the%20on-screen%20image.%20If%20your%20frame%20rate%20is%20below%2060%20FPS%2C%20you'll%20see%20some%20frames%20of%20animation%20repeated%2C%20and%20it%20can%20potentially%20create%20screen%20tearing%20and%20other%20graphical%20glitches%20if%20your%20monitor%20is%20loading%20frames%20at%20an%20uneven%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20midrange%20gaming%20computers%20are%20fully%20capable%20of%20reaching%20frame%20rates%20beyond%2060%20FPS%20in%20many%20games%2C%20but%20it's%20really%20only%20a%20benefit%20if%20you%20have%20a%20display%20with%20a%20high%20refresh%20rate%20too.%20A%2060Hz%20display%20can%20only%20display%2060%20frames%20per%20second%2C%20and%20while%20more%20frames%20coming%20from%20the%20computer%20will%20still%20mean%20smoother%20animation%2C%20there's%20little%20difference%20to%20the%20naked%20eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20you%20can%20find%20your%20display's%20refresh%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3EClick%20the%20Start%20button%20and%20then%20click%20Settings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20Settings%20window%2C%20click%20System.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThen%20click%20on%20Display%20and%20then%20click%20Advanced%20display%20settings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENote%20the%20monitor's%20refresh%20rate.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Screenshot%20of%20the%20Advanced%20display%20settings%20screen.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62f1722f8677d80018ee6726%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22525%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFind%20your%20display's%20frame%20rate%20in%20System%20Settings.%3Cp%3EDave%20Johnson%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EInstead%20of%20steps%201%20and%202%2C%20you%20can%20right%20click%20on%20an%20empty%20area%20on%20your%20desktop%20and%20select%20%3Cstrong%3EDisplay%20settings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20scroll%20down%2C%20and%20then%20select%20%3Cstrong%3EAdvanced%20display%20settings%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Find%20out%20your%20current%20FPS%5C%22%3EFind%20out%20your%20current%20FPS%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20the%20frame%20rate%20your%20gra