figure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EGlobal%20wealth%20declined%20in%202022%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%202008%2C%20UBS%20and%20Credit%20Suisse%20economists%20said%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAmericans%20were%20hit%20hardest%20as%20stocks%20and%20bonds%20tumbled%20throughout%20the%20year%2C%20the%20banks%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERoughly%201.7%20million%20US%20adults%20lost%20their%20status%20as%20millionaires.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGlobal%20wealth%20declined%20last%20year%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%202008%2C%20and%20Americans%20in%20particular%20took%20the%20biggest%20hit%20as%20stocks%20and%20bonds%20sold%20off%20and%20currencies%20fluctuated%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ubs.com%2Fglobal%2Fen%2Fmedia%2Fdisplay-page-ndp%2Fen-20230815-global-wealth-report-2023.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520latest%2520Global%2520Wealth%2520Report%2Cby%2520Credit%2520Suisse%2520and%2520UBS.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewealth%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20UBS%20and%20Credit%20Suisse%20economists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20about%201.7%20million%20US%20adults%20lost%20their%20status%20as%20millionaires%20in%202022.%20Plus%2C%2017%2C260%20fell%20out%20of%20the%20ultra-high%20net%20worth%20bracket%20of%20those%20worth%20%24100%20million%20or%20more.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20crashed%20by%2019%25%20in%202022%2C%20and%20it%20was%20one%20of%20the%2010%20worst%20years%20for%20the%20stock%20market%20in%20nine%20decades.%20The%20losses%20erased%20most%20of%20the%20meteoric%20gains%20seen%20in%202021%2C%20when%20the%20market%20grew%20by%20more%20than%2026%25%20and%20wealth%20surged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%5BF%5Dinancial%20assets%20contributed%20most%20to%20wealth%20declines%20in%202022%20while%20non-financial%20assets%20(mostly%20real%20estate)%20stayed%20resilient%2C%20despite%20rapidly%20rising%20interest%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20economists%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20relative%20contributions%20of%20financial%20and%20non-financial%20assets%20may%20reverse%20in%202023%20if%20house%20prices%20decline%20in%20response%20to%20higher%20interest%20rates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20in%20total%20dollar%20terms%2C%20global%20wealth%20slipped%202.4%25%20to%20about%20%24454.4%20trillion%2C%20and%20much%20of%20that%20was%20due%20to%20shifting%20currency%20values.%20Europeans%20felt%20the%20bite%20from%20weaker%20currencies%2C%20while%20Russia%20and%20Latin%20America%20benefitted%20from%20the%20shifts.%20Russia%2C%20amid%20its%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20added%2056%2C000%20millionaire%20amid%20a%20strengthening%20of%20the%20ruble.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Switzerland%20and%20Hong%20Kong%20boasted%20the%20highest%20level%20of%20wealth%20per%20adult.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20country%20by%20country%20basis%2C%20the%20US%20saw%20the%20biggest%20losses%20in%202022%2C%20as%20the%20country%20shed%20%245.9%20trillion%2C%20compared%20to%20its%20%2419.5%20trillion%20rise%20the%20prior%20year.%20Japan%2C%20China%2C%20Canada%2C%20and%20Australia%20also%20saw%20losses%20exceeding%20%241%20trillion.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20banks%20project%20that%20global%20wealth%20will%20rise%20by%2038%25%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years%20to%20hit%20%24629%20trillion%20by%202027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGrowth%20by%20middle-income%20countries%20will%20be%20the%20primary%20driver%20of%20global%20trends%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20economists%20maintained.%20%26quot%3BWe%20estimate%20wealth%20per%20adult%20to%20reach%20USD%20110%2C270%20in%202027%20and%20the%20number%20of%20millionaires%20to%20reach%2086%20million%20while%20the%20number%20of%20ultra-high-net-worth%20individuals%20(UHNWIs)%20is%20likely%20to%20rise%20to%20372%2C000%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-wealth-millionaires-2008-ubs-rich