tion%2Fashoka-university-accepts-resignation-of-author-of-paper-on-possible-manipulation-in-2019-polls%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20a%20Peaceful%20Non-Cooperation%20Meeting%20in%20Bombay%20Turned%20Violent%2C%20Leaving%20Gandhi%20Distraught%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15085136%2FCodd-bottle_necks_cropped.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%2031%20July%201921%2C%20Gandhi%20attended%20a%20rally%20in%20the%20compound%20of%20the%20Elphinstone%20Mill%2C%20which%20was%20owned%20by%20the%20Khilafat%20leader%20Umar%20Sobhani.%20Sobhani%20gave%20his%20full%20support%20to%20this%20meeting%20at%20which%20foreign%20cloth%20was%20burnt.%20About%20ten%20to%20twelve%20thousand%20were%20present%2C%20and%20the%20affair%20was%20entirely%20peaceful%20and%20orderly.38%20The%20mood%20began%20to%20shift%20from%20September%201921%20onwards.%20When%20Shaukat%20Ali%20was%20arrested%20that%20month%20there%20were%20spontaneous%20strikes%20in%20certain%20mills%2C%20starting%20on%2017%20September%2C%20with%2019%2C000%20workers%20out%20by%2019%20September.%20They%20returned%20to%20work%20after%20seven%20ringleaders%20were%20arrested.%20There%20was%20a%20further%20bonfire%20of%20foreign%20cloth%20at%20Elphinstone%20Mill%2C%20on%209%20October%201921%2C%20that%20Gandhi%20attended.%20The%20same%20venue%20saw%20another%20such%20ceremony%20staged%20by%20Gandhi%20on%2017%20November%201921%2C%20the%20day%20on%20which%20the%20Prince%20of%20Wales%20landed%20in%20Bombay%20to%20start%20his%20tour%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20321px)%2085vw%2C%20321px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15084613%2FNoncooperation-in-India_Paperback.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22321%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15084613%2FNoncooperation-in-India_Paperback.jpg%20776w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15084613%2FNoncooperation-in-India_Paperback-194x300.jpg%20194w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15084613%2FNoncooperation-in-India_Paperback-662x1024.jpg%20662w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668134%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22497%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDavid%20Hardiman%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3ENoncooperation%20in%20India%3A%20Nonviolent%20Strategy%20and%20Protest%2C%201920-22%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EContext%2FWestland%20Books%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20there%20was%20a%20much%20larger%20turn-out%20than%20on%20the%20previous%20two%20occasions%2C%20with%20an%20estimated%2025%2C000%20workers%20being%20there%20as%20a%20pile%20of%20foreign%20cloth%20was%20lit.%20Gandhi%20addressed%20the%20meeting%2C%20stressing%20the%20need%20for%20nonviolence%20even%20in%20the%20face%20of%20great%20provocation.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20Prince%20of%20Wales%20was%20proceeding%20through%20streets%20lined%20with%20crowds%20of%20cheering%20loyalists%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20many%20of%20whom%20were%20Europeans%2C%20Anglo-Indians%2C%20Parsis%20and%20Jews%20%E2%80%93%20on%20the%20way%20to%20Chowpatty%20Beach.%20When%20the%20meeting%20at%20Elphinstone%20Mill%20ended%2C%20the%20workers%20made%20their%20way%20to%20Charni%20Road%20and%20Marine%20Lines%20stations%20where%20they%20met%20crowds%20of%20loyalists%20returning%20from%20welcoming%20the%20Prince%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20were%20in%20trams.%20The%20workers%20rushed%20the%20trams%2C%20beating%20up%20their%20occupants.%20Many%20trams%20were%20set%20on%20fire.%20Anyone%20wearing%20hats%20that%20were%20seen%20to%20be%20%E2%80%98loyalist%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20solar%20topees%2C%20felt%20hats%2C%20or%20the%20Parsi%20phenta%20%E2%80%93%20was%20singled%20out%20for%20attack.%20Their%20headgear%20was%20snatched%2C%20piled%20up%20in%20the%20street%20and%20burnt.%20Europeans%20and%20Anglo-Indians%20were%20singled%20out%20because%20they%20were%20associated%20with%20the%20mill%20supervisors%20who%20often%20treated%20the%20workers%20in%20a%20racist%20and%20violent%20manner.%20They%20were%20now%20on%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%20the%20kicks%20and%20blows.%20The%20Parsis%20were%20attacked%20because%20they%20were%20known%20for%20their%20loyalism%20to%20the%20British%2C39%20as%20they%20owned%20and%20operated%20several%20mills%2C%20and%20as%20many%20of%20the%20liquor%20shops%20in%20the%20city%20were%20run%20by%20members%20of%20this%20community%20and%20they%20had%20refused%20to%20close%20them%20despite%20nationalist%20picketing.%20The%20relatively%20small%20Jewish%20community%20of%20the%20city%20was%20associated%20with%20the%20capitalist%20elite.%20When%20news%20of%20what%20was%20going%20on%20spread%2C%20workers%20came%20out%20from%20other%20mills%20and%20joined%20the%20fray.%20Some%20were%20heard%20to%20cry%20%E2%80%98Mahatma%20Gandhi%20ki%20jai%E2%80%99%20as%20they%20assaulted%20the%20loyalists.%20Even%20Parsi%20women%20were%20not%20spared%20%E2%80%93%20several%20were%20assaulted%20and%20had%20their%20saris%20torn%20from%20them.%20Two%20Anglo-Indians%2C%20two%20Parsis%2C%20and%20one%20American%20were%20killed%20in%20the%20turmoil.%20During%20the%20disturbance%2C%20four%20liquor%20shops%20were%20burnt%20down%20and%20a%20further%20135%20looted%20or%20damaged%20by%20the%20crowds.%20Intense%20fighting%20continued%20into%20the%20early%20hours%20of%2018%20November%2C%20with%20six%20policemen%20being%20killed.%20Congress%20volunteers%20who%20tried%20to%20stop%20the%20violence%20were%20themselves%20beaten%3B%20some%20so%20badly%20that%20they%20died.%20Although%20martial%20law%20was%20declared%2C%20workers%20continued%20in%20the%20next%20few%20days%20to%20roam%20the%20streets%20attacking%20those%20whose%20headwear%20and%20clothing%20marked%20them%20as%20loyalists.%20Some%20Parsis%20and%20Anglo-Indians%20retaliated%20by%20forming%20their%20own%20bands%2C%20which%20toured%20the%20streets%20snatching%20Gandhi%20caps%20and%20attacking%20people%20considered%20to%20be%20pro-Congress%2C%20while%20the%20police%20looked%20on%20and%20even%20helped%20them.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20nationalist%20leaders%20and%20volunteers%20joined%20with%20groups%20of%20public%20figures%20who%20went%20around%20the%20city%20exhorting%20people%20to%20stop%20the%20violence%2C%20and%20by%20this%20means%20order%20was%20eventually%20restored.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22The%20Constitution%20and%20the%20Wrath%20of%20(We)%20the%20People%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-constitution-and-the-wrath-of-we-the-people%5C%22%3EThe%20Constitution%20and%20the%20Wrath%20of%20(We)%20the%20People%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGandhi%20was%20left%20distraught%20by%20all%20this%2C%20especially%20as%20he%20had%20put%20so%20much%20stress%20on%20the%20need%20for%20complete%20nonviolence%20in%20his%20speech%20that%20day%20to%20the%20workers.%20He%20had%20rushed%20immediately%20to%20the%20scene%20on%20hearing%20of%20the%20rioting%2C%20where%20he%20was%20told%20%E2%80%98the%20most%20painful%20and%20humiliating%20story%20of%20molestation%20of%20Parsi%20sisters%E2%80%99.%20One%20elderly%20Parsi%20pleaded%20with%20him%20to%20save%20them.%20He%20was%20surrounded%20by%20crowds%20chanting%20%E2%80%98Mahatma%20Gandhi%20ki%20jai!%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20sound%20that%20%E2%80%93%20he%20said%20%E2%80%93%20merely%20grated%20on%20his%20ears.%20He%20appealed%20for%20them%20to%20go%20home.%20When%20a%20report%20came%20to%20him%20of%20violence%20in%20another%20part%20of%20the%20city%2C%20he%20went%20there%20and%20called%20for%20calm%2C%20persuading%20the%20crowd%20to%20disperse.%20He%20estimated%20that%20about%2020%2C000%20people%20were%20involved%2C%20and%20not%20all%20were%20mill%20hands.%20He%20felt%20that%20they%20knew%20what%20they%20were%20doing%2C%20being%20%E2%80%98bent%20upon%20mischief%20and%20destruction%E2%80%99.%20He%20wrote%20late%20that%20night%3A%20%E2%80%98We%20have%20a%20foretaste%20of%20swaraj.%20I%20have%20been%20put%20to%20shame.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENext%20day%2C%2018%20November%2C%20he%20reported%20that%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim%20volunteers%20who%20had%20tried%20to%20intervene%20with%20workers%20in%20Parel%20had%20been%20turned%20on.%20He%20had%20personally%20seen%20them%20on%20their%20return%20with%20their%20heads%20broken%20and%20bleeding.%20Some%20had%20%E2%80%98lacerating%20wounds%E2%80%99.%20He%20accused%20the%20mill%20workers%20of%20leaving%20their%20factories%20in%20%E2%80%98criminal%20disobedience%20of%20the%20wishes%20of%20their%20masters%E2%80%99.%20%E2%80%98We%20claim%20to%20have%20established%20a%20peaceful%20atmosphere%2C%20i.e.%2C%20to%20have%20attained%20by%20our%20non-violence%20sufficient%20control%20over%20the%20people%20to%20keep%20their%20violence%20under%20check.%20We%20have%20failed%20when%20we%20ought%20to%20have%20succeeded.%E2%80%99%20He%20felt%20personally%20culpable%2C%20as%20he%20had%20encouraged%20a%20spirit%20of%20defiance%20that%20he%20had%20been%20unable%20to%C2%A0control.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarly%20next%20morning%2C%20Gandhi%20announced%20that%20he%20was%20to%20go%20on%20a%20fast%20until%20peace%20had%20been%20restored%20between%20the%20different%20communities.%20He%20stated%3A%20%E2%80%98The%20swaraj%20that%20I%20have%20witnessed%20during%20the%20last%20two%20days%20has%20stunk%20in%20my%20nostrils%E2%80%99.%20The%20fast%20continued%20during%20the%2020th%20and%2021st%20as%20he%20issued%20appeals%20for%20peace.%20The%20riots%20had%20subsided%20by%2022%20November%2C%20and%20he%20broke%20his%20fast%20that%20morning.%20A%20meeting%20of%20the%20Congress%20Working%20Committee%20was%20held%20in%20the%20city%20on%2022%20and%2023%20November%20at%20which%20the%20violence%20was%20deplored.%20The%20committee%20felt%2C%20nonetheless%2C%20that%20it%20had%20exposed%20a%20%E2%80%98weak%20spot%E2%80%99%20that%20revealed%20a%20need%20for%20efforts%20to%20obtain%20better%20control%20over%20%E2%80%98all%20turbulent%20elements%20in%20society%E2%80%99.%20Congress%20outposts%20were%20to%20be%20established%20%E2%80%98in%20every%20street%2C%20in%20every%20lane%E2%80%99%20in%20which%20volunteers%20would%20be%20based%20who%20would%20maintain%20peace.%20Only%20those%20who%20had%20taken%20a%20pledge%20of%20nonviolence%20were%20to%20serve%20in%20such%20a%20capacity.%20Gandhi%20left%20Bombay%20on%2026%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExtracted%20with%20permission%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3ENoncooperation%20in%20India%3Cem%3E%20by%20David%20Hardiman%2C%20first%20published%20by%20Context%2C%20an%20imprint%20of%20Westland%20Books.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692070207000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15085136%2FCodd-bottle_necks_cropped.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fwhen-a-peaceful-non-cooperation-meeting-in-bombay-turned-violent-leaving-gandhi-distraught%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Troublemakers%20attacked%20Europeans%20and%20even%20Parsis%2C%20Anglo-Indians%20and%20Jews%20whom%20they%20saw%20as%20%E2%80%98loyalists%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20Empire.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fwhen-a-peaceful-non-cooperation-meeting-in-bombay-turned-violent-leaving-gandhi-distraught%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fire%20at%20petrol%20station%20in%20Russia%20kills%2030%20including%20three%20children%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692060180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F08%2F1600x900%2Fskynews-russia-petrol-station_6251220.jpg%3F20230815082046%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ffire-at-petrol-station-in-russia-kills-25-including-three-children-12940274%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%2